comment:
* A {@link CinematicEffectResponse} include textured meshes
 * and camera attributes of key frames.
 *
 * @hide

variables.name: CINEMATIC_EFFECT_STATUS_ERROR
variables.comment: Cinematic effect generation failure with generic error.

variables.name: CINEMATIC_EFFECT_STATUS_NOT_READY
variables.comment:
* Service not ready for cinematic effect generation, e.g. a
     * dependency is unavailable.

variables.name: CINEMATIC_EFFECT_STATUS_PENDING
variables.comment:
* There is already a task being processed for the same task id.
     * Client should wait for the response and not send the same request
     * again.

variables.name: CINEMATIC_EFFECT_STATUS_TOO_MANY_REQUESTS
variables.comment: Too many requests (with different task id) for server to handle.

variables.name: CINEMATIC_EFFECT_STATUS_FEATURE_DISABLED
variables.comment: Feature is disabled, for example, in an emergency situation.

variables.name: CINEMATIC_EFFECT_STATUS_IMAGE_FORMAT_NOT_SUITABLE
variables.comment: Image format related problems (i.e. resolution or aspect ratio problems).

variables.name: CINEMATIC_EFFECT_STATUS_CONTENT_UNSUPPORTED
variables.comment:
* The cinematic effect feature is not supported on certain types of images,
     * for example, some implementation only support portrait.

variables.name: CINEMATIC_EFFECT_STATUS_CONTENT_TARGET_ERROR
variables.comment:
* Cannot generate cinematic effect with the targets on the image, for example,
     * too many targets on the image.

variables.name: CINEMATIC_EFFECT_STATUS_CONTENT_TOO_FLAT
variables.comment: Image is too flat to generate cinematic effect.

variables.name: CINEMATIC_EFFECT_STATUS_ANIMATION_FAILURE
variables.comment: Something is wrong with generating animation.

variables.name: IMAGE_CONTENT_TYPE_OTHER
variables.comment: Image content is not people portrait or landscape.

variables.name: mTaskId
variables.comment: The id of the cinematic effect generation task.

variables.name: mTexturedMeshes
variables.comment: The textured mesh required to render cinematic effect.

variables.name: mStartKeyFrame
variables.comment: The start camera position for animation.

variables.name: mEndKeyFrame
variables.comment: The end camera position for animation.

methods.name: public int getStatusCode()
methods.comment: Gets the cinematic effect generation status code.

methods.name: public int getImageContentType()
methods.comment:
* Get the image content type, which briefly classifies what's
     * the content of image, like people portrait, landscape etc.

methods.name: public CameraAttributes getStartKeyFrame()
methods.comment:
* Get the camera attributes (position info and other parameters, see docs of
     * {@link CameraAttributes}) of the start key frame on the animation path.

methods.name: public CameraAttributes getEndKeyFrame()
methods.comment:
* Get the camera attributes (position info and other parameters, see docs of
     * {@link CameraAttributes}) of the end key frame on the animation path.

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel out, int flags)

methodNames: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel out, int flags)
